[http://forums.whirlpool.net.au/archive/447641 On whirlpool.net.au]
This device was used by '''Frontier Communications'''. It appears to be pictured as using a TNETD7300AGDW processor in the FCC photos.
The default SSID pattern for the device appears to be the unit's MAC address (upper case hex digits, no delimiters). :A sample SSID is '''0013A39FA345''' where the MAC on the label is 00:13:A3:9F:A3:45 and the BSSID is 00:13:A3:9F:A3:4B.
